  "response_text": "# Good Post-Workout Meals for Muscle Building\n\n**Key components:**\n- **Protein** (20-40g) to repair muscle tissue\n- **Carbs** to replenish glycogen stores\n- **Some fat** for hormone production\n\n**Practical examples:**\n- Chicken breast with rice and vegetables\n- Greek yogurt with granola and berries\n- Salmon with sweet potato\n- Turkey sandwich on whole grain bread\n- Protein shake with banana and oats\n- Eggs with toast and avocado\n- Cottage cheese with fruit\n\n**Timing tip:** Eating within 1-2 hours post-workout is ideal, though total daily protein intake matters more than exact timing.\n\n**Quick options** if you're short on time:\n- Protein powder mixed with milk and fruit\n- Canned tuna with crackers\n- String cheese and an apple\n\nThe \"best\" meal depends on your preferences and what you can digest comfortably. Consistency with adequate protein throughout the day matters more than any single meal.",
